#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:1
msgid "RPP Architecture"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:3
msgid ""
"The **Rules–Policy–Parameters (RPP)** pattern is the architectural framework "
"for separating government business rule concerns into three distinct, "
"independently governable layers."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:7
msgid "The three layers"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:9
msgid ""
"LAW (legislation)\n"
"  ↓\n"
"POLICY — Normative values extracted from the law (cprmv:Rule)\n"
"  ↓  implements\n"
"RULES — Executable decision logic that operationalises policy (cpsv:Rule, "
"ronl:TemporalRule)\n"
"  ↓  configured by\n"
"PARAMETERS — Tunable constants that adjust rule behaviour "
"(ronl:ParameterWaarde)\n"
"  ↓\n"
"DECISION — Computed outcome for a citizen or case"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:21
msgid "Policy layer"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:23
msgid ""
"Policy captures what the law **mandates** — the normative values that must "
"be implemented. It is expressed as `cprmv:Rule` and sourced from legal "
"analysis. Policy is owned by legal and policy teams and changes when "
"legislation changes."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:25
msgid ""
"Examples: the legal definition of \"eligible for zorgtoeslag\", the "
"statutory AOW retirement age formula."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:27
msgid "Rules layer"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:29
msgid ""
"Rules capture **how** policy is implemented computationally — the executable "
"decision logic. Expressed as `cpsv:Rule, ronl:TemporalRule`, rules are time-"
"bounded and link back to their policy source via `ronl:extends`. Rules are "
"owned by business analysts and are versioned independently of the underlying "
"policy."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:31
msgid ""
"Examples: an eligibility check function, a benefit calculation algorithm."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:33
msgid "Parameters layer"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:35
msgid ""
"Parameters are **configurable constants** that tune rule behaviour without "
"requiring rule changes. Expressed as `ronl:ParameterWaarde`, parameters "
"carry a machine-readable notation, a value, a unit, and temporal validity. "
"They are owned by operational teams who can update them within authorised "
"ranges."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:37
msgid ""
"Examples: an income threshold, a regional pilot adjustment factor, a "
"standard premium amount."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:41
msgid "Semantic linking"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:43
msgid "The RPP layers are connected through explicit RDF properties:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:45
msgid ""
"# Policy rule — linked to legislation\n"
"<.../rules/aow-leeftijd-policy>\n"
"    a cprmv:Rule ;\n"
"    cprmv:implements <https://wetten.overheid.nl/BWBR0002221> .\n"
"\n"
"# Temporal rule — links to policy via ronl:extends\n"
"<.../rules/aow-leeftijd-2024>\n"
"    a cpsv:Rule, ronl:TemporalRule ;\n"
"    ronl:extends <https://wetten.overheid.nl/BWBR0002221/2024-01-01/0/"
"artikel/7a> ;\n"
"    ronl:validFrom \"2024-01-01\"^^xsd:date ;\n"
"    ronl:validUntil \"2024-12-31\"^^xsd:date .\n"
"\n"
"# Parameter — used by the rule\n"
"<.../parameters/aow-standaard-leeftijd>\n"
"    a ronl:ParameterWaarde ;\n"
"    skos:notation \"AOW_LEEFTIJD_STANDAARD\" ;\n"
"    schema:value \"67\" ;\n"
"    schema:unitCode \"ANN\" ."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:68
msgid "Governance benefits"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:70
msgid ""
"**Legal traceability.** Every decision can be traced from output back to the "
"specific legal article that mandates it. When a SPARQL query links "
"`cprmv:DecisionRule → cprmv:extends → eli:LegalResource`, the chain from "
"decision to law is explicit and machine-verifiable."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:72
msgid ""
"**Organisational agility.** Parameters can be updated by operational teams "
"within their authorised scope, without touching rules (which require analyst "
"approval) or policy (which requires legal approval). This reduces the cost "
"and risk of routine maintenance."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:74
msgid ""
"**Governance clarity.** Each layer has a distinct approval workflow and "
"ownership. Changes to policy require legal sign-off. Changes to rules "
"require analyst review. Changes to parameters are self-service within "
"defined bounds."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:76
msgid ""
"**Version control compatibility.** Because each layer is expressed as "
"separate entities in the Turtle file, git diffs are scoped to the layer that "
"actually changed — a parameter update does not create noise in the rules or "
"policy sections."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:80
msgid "Implementation in the editor"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:82
msgid ""
"The three RPP tabs are visually differentiated with colour coding and "
"explanatory banners. Each tab displays its RPP layer label and a brief "
"explanation of how that layer relates to the others."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Crpp-architecture.md:84
msgid ""
"The `cprmv:implements` property (v1.9.0) creates automatic semantic linking "
"between CPRMV policy rules and their legal resource, without requiring "
"manual user configuration."
msgstr ""
